                                "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                                "subject": "Inspiration"
                            },
                            "text": "Pan, whose father is Hermes and whose mother is a daughter of Dryops, is a capricious nature deity in Greek mythology. The god of shepherds and flocks is often depicted as a man with a bearded face and the hindquarters and hooves of a goat, like the satyrs he is often associated with. It is said that seeing him with his true appearance in your dreams is a sign of happiness."
                        },
